uEtsDetails":null},{"portName":"Panama Canal","displayOrder":2,"co2":442.324328000000000000,"eeoi":7.207455987364800000,"aer":5.799697080243505000,"soxMt":8.610720000000000000,"sox":0.140307420349535530,"noxMt":14.148200000000001000,"nox":0.230537916061525520,"euEtsDetails":null},{"portName":"Beaumont","displayOrder":1,"co2":675.912399999999900000,"eeoi":8.683800989132486000,"aer":6.987682662284460000,"soxMt":8.894800000000002000,"sox":0.114276159215507310,"noxMt":21.440000000000000000,"nox":0.275450921165228700,"euEtsDetails":null},{"portName":"Ulsan","displayOrder":4,"co2":100.989000000000000000,"eeoi":16.285792830949780000,"aer":13.104854930323889000,"soxMt":0.063000000000000010,"sox":0.010159571323112779,"noxMt":3.150000000000000400,"nox":0.507978566155638900,"euEtsDetails":null},{"portName":"New York, NY","displayOrder":0,"co2":0.000000000000000000,"eeoi":0.000000000000000000,"aer":0.000000000000000000,"soxMt":0.000000000000000000,"sox":0.000000000000000000,"noxMt":0.000000000000000000,"nox":0.000000000000000000,"euEtsDetails":null}]},"remarkList":[{"modifiedDate":"2022-10-05T15:28:23.957","modifiedByFull":"Ervasti, Josh","remark":"Bunker desk closed additional $65k hedge profit for month of September under this voyage"},{"modifiedDate":"2022-08-12T19:57:54.193","modifiedByFull":"Ervasti, Josh","remark":"Despite running late and having to ask for extension twice to the laycan, this was a very good voyage for us in the end as the rest of the voyage went all in our favor.  \n\n\u2022\tCleaning cost estimated $65k and all went perfectly (no additional cleaning needed) so cost came in less at $50k.  \n\u2022\tHad to go max speed south and cut through ECA for shortest ballast.  This in addition to Japan/Korea steaming did end up resulting in significant additional LSGO consumed but laden performance was very good and total bunker was only $36k over the estimate.  \n\u2022\tFirst time calling Beaumont for loading on Proman COA.  Initial PDA included nearly $70k of wharfage/dockage (worldscale costs not covered in CP) but much to my delight, FDA reflected that agents made a mistake referring to a different dock.  \no\tActual Beaumont cost $51k vs $120k est.\n\u2022\tBeing late for laycan we had to take a huge gamble on prebooking canal without a new laycan or loading prospects.  Initially looked like 4 days waiting at canal on our dime but delays at loadport turned that into demurrage and only 1 day wait at canal\n\u2022\tAdditional disport Ulsan added with 2 berths which adds $58k to result\n\u2022\tTokuyama/Ptaek both came in less than estimated on FDA ($35k less on total)\n\u2022\tBunker hedge wasn\u2019t finalized at time of fixing but actual profit came in better than estimated.  ($263k profit vs $207k est)\n\u2022\tBasically pristine weather on crossing where we averaged 12.7 kts (2% wx against 10% est) even with having to slow down one day to let tropical storm get ahead of us.\n\u2022\t2.5 days on demurrage (21.5kpdy) adds $53k to result."},{"modifiedDate":"2022-08-01T17:04:34.193","modifiedByFull":"Ervasti, Josh","remark":"Port costs adjusted, much less than estimated, also laden bunkers entered upon arrival tokuyama less than estimated"},{"modifiedDate":"2022-06-30T19:33:35.723","modifiedByFull":"Ervasti, Josh","remark":"Panama completed, bunkers a bit less than estimated, cleaning cost adjusted to actual, tc chems estimated"},{"modifiedDate":"2022-06-24T15:53:16.363","modifiedByFull":"Ervasti, Josh","remark":"port arthur extended stay - increased LSGO consumption - 2 days dem/2 less days waiting at canal"},{"modifiedDate":"2022-06-17T17:34:37.993","modifiedByFull":"Ervasti, Josh","remark":"hedge profit adjusted to the positive, add\u0027l disport korea added, ballast bunkers adjusted w/ included cleaning costs"}],"offhireList":[],"tcNumber":null,"tcOutIdEncrypted":null,"tcReletDetail":null}